FAQ: How Should I Learn DDD If I'm a Code-First Developer?

In this video message, I provide guidance on how code-first developers can approach implementing a Domain-Driven Design (DDD) architecture for an API or frontend app. I explain the importance of going through the phases of craftship and gaining context before diving into DDD. I discuss various tools and techniques, such as impact mapping, event storming, and process modeling, that can help developers understand the domain and structure their architecture. I emphasize the significance of starting with best practices, learning how to write tests, and gradually incorporating DDD patterns. By following this approach, developers can build a solid foundation and effectively leverage DDD concepts.

  • 00:00 Introduction and Importance of Context
  • 00:49 The Guess Points and Value-First Phase
  • 01:37 Tools and Techniques for Understanding the Domain
  • 02:21 The Phases of Craftship and Systems Thinking
  • 04:19 Moving Towards the Pattern-First Phase
  • 06:47 The Ideal Developer Workflow
